Research questions

Q1: Is there a general factor that could be derived from various aspects of students peer-relations within the classroom?

Q1a: On an individual level: Is it possible to conflate various aspects of students peer-relations within the classroom into one distinct general factor (social-relational situation)?

Q1b: On a classroom level: Is it possible to conflate the classroom means of various aspects of students peer-relations into on distinct general factor (social-relational classroom climate)?

Q2: What is the connection between students behavioral problems and various aspects of their peer-relations?

Q2a: On an individual level: To what extend can students behavioral problems in a class be explained by means of various aspects of their peer-relations?

Q2b: On a classroom level: To what extend can the average amount of behavioral problems in a classroom be explained by classroom means of various aspects of students peer-relations?

Q2c: To what extend do classroom means of various aspects of students peer-relations contribute to individual behavioral classroom problems?

Add on questions(probably they will be dropped later :-) )

Q3a: Can we find profiles of components of social-emotional wellbeing? Q3b: Can we find profiles of components of social-emotional classclimate? Q3c: What is the nexus between the profiles of social-emotional wellbeing and behavioral problems? Q3c: What is the nexus between the profiles of social-emotional classclimate and behavioral problems?
